** access to raw Iranian Household Income and Expenditure Survey (HIES) data**  
from 1363 to 1402 (1984–2024) – published by the Statistical Center of Iran.
 Installation
# Install the latest version
remotes::install_github(
  "hosseinii-sanaa/IHBS",
  subdir = "packages/rhbsirdata"
)
library(rhbsirdata)

Usage Examples
 1. Load raw expenditure data (full detail)
d1 <- load_expenditure(1390, summarise = FALSE)
head(d1)
 2. Load summarized income data at household level
d2 <- load_income(1399, summarise = TRUE)
head(d2)
 3. Add final household weights
d3 <- hbsir.add_weight(d2)
head(d3)
 4. Add demographic attributes (province, urban/rural, etc.)
d4 <- hbsir.add_attributes(d3)
head(d4)
 5. Add commodity classification (COICOP)
d5 <- load_expenditure(1370, summarise = FALSE)
d5 <- hbsir.add_classification(d5,
                               code_col = "Commodity_Code",
                               classification_type = "commodity")
head(d5)
 6. Add industry & occupation classification (ISIC / ISCO)
d6 <- load_income(1380, summarise = FALSE)
d6 <- hbsir.add_classification(d6, code_col = "Industry_Code",   classification_type = "industry")
d6 <- hbsir.add_classification(d6, code_col = "Occupation_Code", classification_type = "occupation")
head(d6)
 7. Add income percentiles, deciles, and quantiles
d7 <- hbsir_add_percentile_decile_quantile(d2, column = "Gross_Income")
head(d7)
 8. Add expenditure percentiles/deciles
d8 <- hbsir_add_percentile_decile_quantile(d1, column = "Gross_Expenditure")
head(d8)

Available Years
1363–1402 (1984–2024) – both income and expenditure surveys.

Key Features:
Local caching (never re-downloads the same year)
Full compatibility with dplyr, arrow, data.table
Helper functions for weights, classifications, and inequality measures
Clean, documented, and CRAN-ready code

For Contributors & Team Use
This package lives inside the internal IHBS monorepo at:
packages/rhbsirdata/
Feel free to update, improve documentation, or add new helper functions!
